                <note rend="inline" type="source">033.1120 H 87/67d: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in Brazil</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Morgan</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1922-07-31T16:00:00-04:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">July 31, 1922—4 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>97. Department’s No. 86, July 18, 6 p.m.<note n="16" xml:id="d399fn16">Not
                        printed.</note>
                </p>
                <p>After consultation with Brazilian Ambassador it has been decided that the Special
                    Mission headed by the Secretary of State will proceed to Rio on the steamship
                        <hi rend="italic">Pan American</hi> from New York about August 24th,
                    arriving off Rio de Janeiro about September 4th. The party will board the U. S.
                    S. <hi rend="italic">Maryland</hi> on the morning of September 5th and enter the
                    harbor that morning. The Commission will leave Rio de Janeiro for the United
                    States on the steamship <hi rend="italic">American Legion</hi> on September
                    11th.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hughes</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
